ude_hidden", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "recursive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "norm_paths", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "case_sensitive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sep", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a list of paths matching a pathname pattern.\n\nThe pattern may contain simple shell-style wildcards a la\nfnmatch. However, unlike fnmatch, filenames starting with a\ndot are special cases that are not matched by '\\*' and '?'\npatterns.\n\nIf `include_hidden` is True, then files and folders starting with\na dot are also returned.\n"]}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.iglob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pathname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "with_matches", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "include_hidden", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "recursive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "norm_paths", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "case_sensitive", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sep", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return an iterator which yields the paths matching a pathname\npattern.\n\nThe pattern may contain simple shell-style wildcards a la\nfnmatch. However, unlike fnmatch, filenames starting with a\ndot are special cases that are not matched by '\\*' and '?'\npatterns.\n\nIf `with_matches` is True, then for each matching path\na 2-tuple will be returned; the second element if the tuple\nwill be a list of the parts of the path that matched the individual\nwildcards.\n\nIf `include_hidden` is True, then files and folders starting with\na dot are also returned.\n"]}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber._iglob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pathname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rootcall", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "include_hidden", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "norm_paths", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "case_sensitive", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sep", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Internal implementation that backs {meth}`iglob`.\n\n`rootcall` is required to differentiate between the user's call to\niglob(), and subsequent recursive calls, for the purposes of resolving\ncertain special cases of \\*\\* wildcards. Specifically, \"\\*\\*\" is supposed\nto include the current directory for purposes of globbing, but the\ndirectory itself should never be returned. So if \\*\\* is the lastmost\npart of the `pathname` given the user to the root call, we want to\nignore the current directory. For this, we need to know which the root\ncall is.\n"]}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.resolve_pattern", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dirname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pattern", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "globstar_with_root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "include_hidden", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "norm_paths", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "case_sensitive", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sep", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Apply `pattern` (contains no path elements) to the\nliteral directory in `dirname`.\n\nIf pattern=='', this will filter for directories. This is\na special case that happens when the user's glob expression ends\nwith a slash (in which case we only want directories). It simpler\nand faster to filter here than in {meth}`_iglob`.\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.listdir", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.isdir", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.islink", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "glob2.impl.Globber.exists", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}]}